Author: meatspoon#7860
Content: @Deleted User is right.  What happened in the US was government allowing/encouraging banks to issue loans to anyone and everyone for home purchases.  Then the banks packaged that toxic debt into bullshit debt instruments and resold it in a deceptive way.  So you had 1) a lot of Americans over-extending on their home purchases and 2) institutions and individuals setting themselves up to get rekt by buying the toxic debt.  This is a lot different than a communist government throwing a lot of fiat at crappy housing in an attempt to centrally plan the lives of its tax livestock.

Author: meatspoon#7860
Content: In a sense the Chinese citizens are on the hook all the same since the Yuan, just like any fiat, is debt created and pinned on the public.  But the dynamic of the Chinese housing bubble is quite different and will likely play out differently
